					<description><![CDATA[<p>Sharon AI Raises Major Financing for AI Infrastructure Growth Sharon AI has raised US$1.6 billion in private placement financing to expand its AI computing infrastructure footprint. The Australian neocloud provider</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/sharon-ai-raises-1-6-billion-ai-factory-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal">Sharon AI Raises US$1.6 Billion to Expand AI Factory Infrastructure</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Sharon AI Raises Major Financing for AI Infrastructure Growth</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Sharon AI has raised US$1.6 billion in private placement financing to expand its AI computing infrastructure footprint. The Australian neocloud provider structured the transaction through a combination of equity financing and convertible senior notes.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The financing includes approximately US$900 million from common stock and pre-funded warrant issuances. An additional US$700 million comes from 4.75% Convertible Senior Notes due in 2032. The transaction was anchored by Situational Awareness and funds managed by Oaktree Capital Management.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company plans to use the proceeds to support its previously announced six-year strategic compute collaboration with NVIDIA. That partnership includes the deployment of one of Australia’s largest AI Factory developments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Chief Executive Officer James Manning said demand for GPU computing continues to exceed available supply. He highlighted growing interest from enterprise customers, governments, research organisations, </span><a href="https://www.denodo.com/en/glossary/hyperscalers-definition-importance-key-providers" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">hyperscalers</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, and AI-focused businesses.</span></p>
<h2><b>NVIDIA Partnership Drives AI Factory Expansion</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">A significant portion of the funding will support Sharon AI’s infrastructure buildout plans. The company intends to deploy up to 40,000 NVIDIA Grace Blackwell GB300 GPUs through its strategic collaboration with NVIDIA.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Sharon AI’s total AI Factory capacity has now expanded to 132MW. The company stated that 102 MW of the capacity has already been committed to end users. This shows high market demand for AI computing resources that offer high performance.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More than 55,000 NVIDIA GPUs is expected to be in deployment by mid 2027. The sites will be used for sovereign AI and High Performance Computing services across Australia and the rest of Asia Pacific.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Global demand for AI infrastructure is on the rise. The ability for organizations to access high-performance compute capabilities is essential for training models, for inferencing, research work and business applications of AI.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company believes that this trend will continue as the adoption of AI across industries accelerates. The recent investment has enabled them to begin building out their capacity ahead of demand.</span></p>
<h2><b>Investors Back Long-Term Compute Strategy<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_202925" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202925" class="size-full wp-image-202925" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/a-futuristic-neon-lit-digital-poster-dep_vo34INuRVeuOIctjpfh-Nw_qAciHoIRQ0O0kFqxqWDv_A.png" alt="A neon futuristic visual showing AI-powered financial systems managing large-scale investment flows alongside advanced cloud computing infrastructure with GPUs and CPUs." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-202925" class="wp-caption-text">Sharon AI secures major funding to expand AI infrastructure and scale cloud-based compute services. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The financing attracted support from both new and existing institutional investors. Oaktree Capital Management joined the transaction alongside Situational Awareness and other strategic backers.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The equity portion involved the issuance of nearly 6.7 million common shares priced at US$68.73 per share. Sharon AI also issued pre-funded warrants linked to more than 6.3 million additional shares.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Alongside the equity raise, the company issued US$700 million of Convertible Senior Notes. These notes carry a 4.75% annual interest rate and mature in June 2032. The initial conversion price was set at approximately US$99.66 per share.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The structure provides Sharon AI with substantial growth capital while offering investors exposure to future upside. At the same time, the financing introduces potential future share dilution through warrant exercises and note conversions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Management views the transaction as a strategic step toward building large-scale AI infrastructure. The company continues to position itself as a major provider of cloud-based GPU and CPU compute services.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/behavox-raises-175m-ai-compliance-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Behavox Raises $175M to Expand AI-Native Compliance Platform</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Regional AI Demand Fuels Capacity Investments</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Sharon AI operates within a rapidly expanding AI infrastructure market. Businesses and governments across Asia-Pacific are increasing investments in sovereign computing capabilities and AI development programmes.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s AI Factory model focuses on providing large-scale computing resources through dedicated facilities. These centres are designed to support advanced machine learning workloads and cloud-based AI services.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Management believes regional demand remains significantly underserved. Existing GPU supply constraints continue to challenge organisations seeking access to high-performance computing capacity.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The latest financing enables Sharon AI to accelerate deployment timelines and strengthen its market position. The company aims to become a leading provider of AI infrastructure across Australia and neighbouring markets.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Financial advisers on the transaction included Goldman Sachs as lead placement agent, alongside Lucid Capital Markets and Macquarie Capital. Following completion, Sharon AI expects to continue expanding both capacity and customer commitments throughout the region.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding represents one of the largest AI infrastructure financings announced in Australia. It highlights growing investor confidence in the long-term demand for cloud-based AI computing and sovereign technology infrastructure.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/sharon-ai-raises-1-6-billion-ai-factory-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal">Sharon AI Raises US$1.6 Billion to Expand AI Factory Infrastructure</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
