					<description><![CDATA[<p>Odyssey has raised a major $310 million Series B funding round, pushing the valuation to $1.45 billion for the world model developer. This enormous funding marks a big tactical shift</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/odyssey-raises-310m-shifts-focus-to-amazon-and-imd/" data-wpel-link="internal">Odyssey Raises $310M, Shifts Focus to Amazon and IMD</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Odyssey has raised a major $310 million Series B </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/deepseek-raises-7-4b-at-50b-in-founder-led-deal/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round, pushing the valuation to $1.45 billion for the world model developer. This enormous funding marks a big tactical shift for the company as it moves away from relying mainly on Nvidia to provide AWS and cutting-edge AMD hardware.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Natural Capital, a global leader with broad support from technology heavyweights and a defence-orientated fund consortium, led the oversubscribed funding round. All new names, as well as backers making their return, were </span><a href="https://www.amazon.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Amazon</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, AMD Ventures, Google&#8217;s corporate venture fund GV, EQT, and In-Q-Tel (IQT, the venture capital outfit affiliated with the U.S. Central Intelligence Agency).</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Anyone But Nvidia Shift</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The most striking element of Odyssey’s Series B isn&#8217;t just the dollar amount but who is missing from the list. Only four months prior, Nvidia&#8217;s venture arm, NVentures, led Odyssey&#8217;s Series A round. By actively shifting its core alliances to Amazon and AMD for its Series B, Odyssey has positioned itself at the forefront of a growing &#8220;anyone-but-Nvidia&#8221; movement among high-compute AI startups looking to diversify away from the market leader&#8217;s strict supply-chain dominance.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As part of the massive financial agreement, AWS officially becomes Odyssey’s preferred cloud provider. Crucially, Odyssey will bypass standard Nvidia H100 or Blackwell setups in favour of deploying Amazon’s custom Trainium chips and processing architectures to train its next-generation models.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_202923" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202923" class="size-large wp-image-202923" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/AI-7-1024x853.jpg" alt="AI" width="1024" height="853" /><p id="caption-attachment-202923" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;This round provides the compute, infrastructure, and partners required to push the absolute frontier of general world models,&#8221; said Oliver Cameron, co-founder and CEO of Odyssey. &#8220;Our goal is to achieve a true &#8216;GPT-3 moment&#8217; for the field of environmental simulation, and our deep operational partnerships with Amazon and AMD give us the specialised physical infrastructure to run these intense workloads at scale.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News:</span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/deepseek-raises-7-4b-at-50b-in-founder-led-deal/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400"> DeepSeek Raises $7.4B at $50B+ in Founder-Led Deal</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Beyond Language: The Era of World Models</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded in late 2023 by autonomous vehicle veterans Oliver Cameron (former executive at Cruise and Voyage) and Jeff Hawke (founding engineer at driverless pioneer Wayve), Odyssey was born out of a fundamental limitation in current AI technology. While Large Language Models (LLMs) excel at predicting the next word in a sentence, they possess no innate understanding of physical reality, spatial constraints, or cause-and-effect relationships.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Odyssey is building world models, generative AI systems that learn physics, environmental dynamics, and spatial geometry. Rather than being trained on internet text, Odyssey&#8217;s models are trained on rich visual, spatial, and physical data. The resulting systems can simulate highly persistent, real-time 3D worlds that behave according to the laws of physics.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s roughly 55-person technical staff, split across Palo Alto, London, and Zurich, includes elite alumni from DeepMind, Tesla, Waymo, and Apple. The team is currently building out specialised systems like Odyssey-2 Max, optimised for high-fidelity physics simulation, and Agora-1, a breakthrough architecture that allows multiple independent AI agents to interact dynamically inside a single, shared simulated environment.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A Crowded, High-Stakes Race</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With this raise, Odyssey lands squarely in the upper echelons of a fiercely competitive and highly capitalised race to master physical AI simulation. The startup will be competing directly for enterprise dominance against Fei-Fei Li&#8217;s World Labs (which recently raised $230 million), generative video leader Runway (valued at $5.3 billion), and Google DeepMind&#8217;s specialised Genie model.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The potential applications for Odyssey&#8217;s technology stretch far beyond gaming and virtual worlds. By creating flawless, physics-accurate digital duplicates of reality, an industrial robotics manufacturer could run millions of automated training scenarios inside an Odyssey simulation overnight, mastering complex physical tasks before a robot ever touches a real-world factory floor.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Furthermore, the high-profile inclusion of national security venture fund In-Q-Tel points toward an immediate, highly lucrative demand for advanced world-simulation software within defence logistics, tactical training, and autonomous threat-assessment mapping.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/odyssey-raises-310m-shifts-focus-to-amazon-and-imd/" data-wpel-link="internal">Odyssey Raises $310M, Shifts Focus to Amazon and IMD</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
